The paper discusses improving the intellectual effectiveness of individual AI systems through learning in heterogeneous multiagent systems and mathematical approaches for non-iterative corrections of errors. This suggests a focus on AI and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG), as well as multiagent systems (cs.MA) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the mention of correcting errors in legacy AI systems suggests a potential focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
